body.description: MWE Gold V2 is the next step in the evolution of Cooler Master's entry level 80 PLUS Gold rated efficiency series. This series of power supply units was created to make the transition from White or Bronze rated power supplies to Gold easier and more affordable for end users. To that end, this new generation of MWE Gold units continues this vision with a number of improvements to the original design with a negligible change in price. Cooler Master has implemented meaningful upgrades to the original MWE Gold that will improve the user experience right out of the box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Powerhouse PSU with Impressive Features
reviews.reviewText: The Cooler Master XG850 Plus Platinum ARGB Fully Modular power supply is a true powerhouse that brings top-tier performance and remarkable features to the table.Reliable and Efficient Performance:As an 850W power supply with an 80+ Platinum efficiency rating, this PSU delivers reliable and stable power to handle even the most demanding systems. It efficiently converts AC power to DC power, reducing energy wastage and minimizing heat output.Fully Modular Design:The fully modular design is a game-changer, allowing me to connect only the cables I need for my setup. This keeps the interior of my PC clean and clutter-free, improving airflow and overall aesthetics.High-Quality Components:Cooler Master has equipped the XG850 Plus Platinum with high-quality components, ensuring consistent performance and long-term reliability. It's built to handle heavy usage and maintain its efficiency over time.ARGB Lighting for Style and Customization:The addition of Addressable RGB lighting adds a touch of style to the PSU. The customizable lighting options allow me to sync it with the rest of my setup, creating a harmonious and visually appealing PC environment.Quiet Operation:Thanks to its intelligent fan control system, the PSU operates quietly during regular usage. The fan only ramps up when necessary, keeping noise levels at a minimum.Temperature Control and Protection:The XG850 Plus Platinum features various safety mechanisms, including OVP (Over Voltage Protection), UVP (Under Voltage Protection), OCP (Over Current Protection), OTP (Over Temperature Protection), and OPP (Over Power Protection). These safety features protect both the PSU and the connected components, giving me peace of mind during extended gaming sessions or heavy workloads.Robust Connectivity:With multiple PCIe, SATA, and peripheral connectors, the PSU offers robust connectivity to accommodate a wide range of components and peripherals. It easily supports multi-GPU setups and storage arrays.Advanced Hybrid Cable Management System:The hybrid cable management system combines the benefits of both flat and round cables, providing flexibility and ease of installation. It's a thoughtful design that enhances cable management options.10-Year Warranty:Cooler Master stands behind the quality of the XG850 Plus Platinum, offering an impressive 10-year warranty. It's a testament to the durability and confidence they have in their product.Final Verdict:In conclusion, the Cooler Master XG850 Plus Platinum ARGB Fully Modular power supply is a top-notch choice for enthusiasts and power users. With its robust performance, fully modular design, ARGB lighting, and safety features, it offers an exceptional package that enhances any high-performance system. If you're looking for a PSU that not only provides ample power but also adds a touch of style to your build, the XG850 Plus Platinum is an excellent investment. It's a reliable and efficient powerhouse that has exceeded my expectations, and I highly recommend it to anyone in need of a premium PSU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Modular has its advantages and disadvantages
reviews.reviewText: this was the 1st time using a modular power supply. I like that I don't have extra unused cables but you have to plan ahead and plug everything in before you put the power supply in place then try and cram the thing in there with the nest of stiff cables in the way. It did not come with all the cables I needed since my motherboard needed a 4 pin 12V connector. I ordered the cable and it worked fine but I think they could have thrown in a splitter or a cable that was already split as on option.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Failed 1 month after Amazon Return was up :-(
reviews.reviewText: I purchased from Amazon on 6/14/23I liked the modular cords. That was a nice feature. This power supply is "rated" at 350 watts over my "stock" power supply (500 watt). The power supply was a smidgen larger than the "hole" it was supposed to fit into. I could get it to fit but it was a tricky process. It seemed to be a decent power supply.But after ~70 days it failed. Yesterday it just shut off. I could still see the lights on the motherboard. But it wouldn't power up. I unplugged it for a bit and then turned it back on and it was fine the rest of the day yesterday.Then today it wouldn't ever completely power up. And it almost trashed my SSD because it started to boot then powered off. I tried the unplug trick and it never came back. Would start then shut down almost immediately. Ugh!I swapped it for my old power supply and I'm doing fine again. This computer is an old computer with a new mobo, CPU, memory, etc. I replaced the power supply to be proactive. See how that worked out for me?I though Cooler Master was a good brand. Yes, it has a 5 year warranty. But I have to pay to ship it and do I really want another one of these??? I don't think so. This sucks. I want my money back. It wasn't cheap.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My son is a pc builder and this was the only thing he wanted for Christmas to upgrade his PC. Came packaged securely. Everything was as expected. Great product. Will buy again when he's ready to build another rig.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for money!
reviews.reviewText: I got this when it was on sale 850 V2 for $70. It was a very good deal. I really appreciate this seller!I use this with a power hungry 7900X. The PSU itself is not super quiet. It's ok. My last PSU was able to completely turn off fan, this one is always running at like 500-700rpm or something. But at this price, and 850W (849 of which are available on the 12V rail!). Also, it has only 2 EPS connectors, but you can always buy your own later. At my purchase price, it is great value for money.Product came sealed, but in its brand packaging (no outer Amazon box, which is good for the environment, I guess)Update:1 month later, I still have no problems.I notice the fan is kind of strange. It's not a smooth sound, it's kind of an warbling, like the blade or bearings are unbalanced. It was like this from the start, and has not changed. Also, the fan is supposed to be sucking from the top and blowing out the rear of the case, but if you put your hand over it you can feel it blowing out the top. Very peculiar. It's like the fan "sucks" literally/figuratively. Still, this was an amazing deal, if this lasts 5 years, it gets ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ from me.
Bastante buena, aunque sigo dudando si es de 750w o de 850w, pero es bastante buena.
Payer pour un retour ! quand le produit est défectueux .... 25$ c'est un peu décevant.

I have never really installed a modular power supply before and thought it might be a bit difficult, it was actually easier! Also I installed ALL the included cables but really if you don't need to, you don't have to. I just installed it, but I was very happy with how silent it is and how well it integrated into my system. It was a bit larger than my previous PSU, but everything aligned very well. I would definitely recommend this PSU.
Fast shipping. Couldn't find a cheaper 'brand name' one anywhere else. Can't believe how hard it is to find psu's right after Christmas season. Retail packaging. Everything as it should be.
